<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[46144]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[A contemporary tragicomedy around the crisis]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[“Bartomeu encadenat” by José Sanchis Sinisterra comes to the Grec directed by Antonio Simón and starring Lluís Soler, Manel Barceló and Maria Molins.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif';">In April 2012, at the height of the financial storm raging in Greece, a retired man called Dimitris Christoulas decided to shoot himself in the head in front of the Greek parliament. This incident has inspired the playwright José Sanchis Sinisterra to write “Bartomeu encadenat” (Bartomeu in Chains), a tragicomedy starring Lluís Soler. </span></p>
<p style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif';">The play tells the story of Bartomeu, who tries to return to humanity the treasure that the World Bank, the modern expression of the Olympus of the gods, denies it: dignity. </span></p>
